                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Feb. 9: The Centre is reviewing a bill that exempts 47 academic institutions from most job quotas for Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes, amid fears that the proposed legislation may hurt the UPA in the coming general elections.           
	The department of personnel and training has called a review of the SC/ST (reservation in posts and services) Bill, 2008, tomorrow, to iron out cracks within the government over proposed legislation. The bill was approved by the Rajya Sabha in December 2008.          
	The decision to review the bill has come after the human resource development ministry and the social justice minis- try indicated discomfort with its present form.                  
	 Bhopal (PTI): An infant was found alive after her parents allegedly threw her off a 70-foot-high hillock near Pachmarhi on Sunday. The shawl in which she was wrapped got entangled in a tree branch just before she hit the ground. Passers-by rescued her. The baby has suffered minor injuries.                                                                                                                            
